headline: ConocoPhillips to Hold First-Quarter Earnings Conference Call on Thursday, May 8
summary: HOUSTON, March 27, 2025--ConocoPhillips (NYSE: COP) will host a conference call webcast on Thursday, May 8, 2025, at 12:00 p.m. Eastern time to discuss first-quarter 2025 financial and operating results. The company’s financial and operating results will be released before the market opens on May 8.

headline: ConocoPhillips' Stock Is About as Cheap as It's Been Since 2023. Here's 1 Thing to Know Before You Buy.
summary: Analysts are reporting that ConocoPhillips has a brighter future than past.  The EV/EBITDA (enterprise value/earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization) ratio is a great metric to use to gauge the attractiveness of oil stocks like ConocoPhillips.  When looking at ConocoPhillips' EV/EBITDA ratio, shares don't seem overly cheap, trading at around 6 times EBITDA -- roughly in line with where shares traded at the end of 2023.
